/*
      Request flow from frontend to backend :-
               Frontend (React) -> Controller -> Service -> Repository -> Database

                 Frontend (React) :-
                        The user interacts with the UI.
                        React sends an HTTP request (API) call to the backend .
                             POST /login
                             GET /jobs

                  @Controller :-
                         Receives the HTTP request from frontend . 
                         Handles request mapping using annotations like @RestController .
                             @RestController
                             @RequestMapping("/users")

                             This controller calls the service layer.

                  @Service :-
                          It is the business layer where business logic are solved .
                          It process the data and performs operation . 
                              Validate user
                              Process job application
                              Generate JWT token
*/
